, or beat my head against the wall after losing 90k xp when I'm one kill from levelling, or any of the other associated bullshit.  <br><br>Given that reaction, I don't think I'll be picking up DAoC.  I could care less if there's no cluster hunting in DAoC, or no mission terminals, or no Vulture Squabblers.  I am currently repulsed by the idea of playing anything that takes anywhere near as much of my time as AO did.  Add to that the fact that what I've seen of DAoC didn't thrill me even a little bit, and it's not hard to understand why I won't be playing.<br><br>Now, I WILL admit to the fact that I've contemplated picking it up and trying it for a little while, but the longest I'd think about playing it is for the first free month, and why even bother?  I've got Deus Ex in desperate need of beating, Max Payne is calling my name from the stores, Wolfenstein will be out in the not-too distant future, I'm flirting with the idea of finishing Baldur's Gate finally (if I can handle the 2D graphics at 640x480 res that is...  I doubt I can.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START |I --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tired.gif ALT="|I"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  So my gaming time is gonna be pretty much full for the foreseeable future.<br><br>And that's assuming that games I'm looking forward to don't come out early.  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wizardry8.com/index1.html">Wizardry 8</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is currently complete, and there are plans to launch before the end of the year (which of course they'd never actually put on their front page...  they seem to be update-phobic).  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.shadowbane.com/">Shadowbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> might be out by Christmas, and I WILL have to play that...  If for no other reason than I think I can talk an RL friend into playing, and that sounds like a blast to me.  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.3do.com/mightandmagic/heroes4/">Heroes of Might and Magic 4</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> just might launch this year, although I'm not counting on it...<br><br>So, no, I won't be playing AO <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  OR</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> DAoC.  Too much SP goodness to look forward to.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> edit:  Are we really surprised no one has picked the last choice? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>~Jaqrabbit<br>Aristotle was famous for knowing everything.  He taught that the brain exists only to <br>cool the blood and is not involved in the process of thinking. This is true only of <br>certain persons.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ujaqrabbit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaqrabbit</A> at: 10/5/01 12:44:08 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showNextMessage?topicID=10.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.emailToFriend?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.threadControl?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to